  "prompt": "What is the best iOS calendar app that allows you to cross off EVENTS as you go through the day?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff date, October 2023, there is no calendar app specifically designed to cross off events in the way one might cross off tasks on a to-do list. However, some iOS calendar apps offer features that might serve a similar purpose by allowing you to mark events as completed or customize them in a way that reflects them as done. Here are a few popular iOS calendar apps that you might consider:\n\n1. **Fantastical**: Known for its natural language input and robust features, Fantastical does allow event editing and might have Good integration with reminders can make for a workaround solution, allowing certain reminders to be marked as complete.\n\n2. **Calendars 5 by Readdle**: This app combines tasks and events, allowing you to manage them intuitively. You can manage your tasks alongside your calendar events, providing a way to handle tasks and indicating completion within your schedule.\n\n3. **Google Calendar**: While it doesn't have a specific \"cross off\" feature for events, you can use tasks in integration with the calendar and mark tasks as completed.\n\n4. **Todoist**: While primarily a task manager, Todoist integrates with calendars and allows you to check off tasks when done. If many of your calendar items are tasks, this could be a powerful way to manage completion.\n\n5. **Microsoft Outlook**: With calendar and email built-in, it allows events to be turned into tasks, which can be checked off within the app. \n\nYou might want to explore task management apps or those that integrate tasks and calendars to achieve a true \"cross-off\" experience. Keep in mind app updates and new releases could add such features in the future.",
